post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_37706549_37706791_0": {"length": 44, "quality": 0.88, "section_id": 1920}}, "n3337": {"so_37706549_37706791_0": {"length": 44, "quality": 0.88, "section_id": 1909}}, "n4659": {"so_37706549_37706791_0": {"length": 32, "quality": 0.64, "section_id": 2191}}}, "37706549": {"ViewCount": "143", "Body": "<p>Is it safe to use <code>std::cout</code> in constructors of objects with statc storage duration in C++98 / C++03?</p>\n<p>It seems from this <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/8785008/1608835\">answer</a> that it isn't but it doesn't include any quotes from the standard.</p>\n<p>Is it only safe to do that in C++11 and C++14?</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "37706791", "Title": "std::cout usage in constructors of objects with static storage duration", "CreationDate": "2016-06-08T15:15:42.093", "Id": "37706549", "CommentCount": "6", "LastEditDate": "2017-05-23T11:52:33.780", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "-1", "LastActivityDate": "2016-06-08T15:30:57.653", "Score": "3", "OwnerUserId": "1608835", "Tags": "<c++><c++11><c++14><c++03><c++98>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "37706791": {"Id": "37706791", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>From C++14 (N3797), \u00a727.4p2:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_37706549_37706791_0\">The objects are constructed and the associations are established at some time prior to or during the first\n  time an object of class ios_base::Init is constructed, and in any case before the body of main begins exe-\n  cution.295 The objects are not destroyed during program execution.296 The results of including \n  in a translation unit shall be as if  defined an instance of ios_base::Init with static storage\n  duration. Similarly, the entire program shall behave as if there were at least one instance of ios_base::Init\n  with static storage duration.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>C++98 uses similar terminology, but without the \"as if\" clause.</p>\n<p>Basically, what this <em>forbids</em> is using the following before <code>main</code>:</p>\n<pre><code>#include &lt;ostream&gt;\nextern std::ostream cout;\n</code></pre>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "1405588", "LastActivityDate": "2016-06-08T15:30:57.653", "Score": "2", "CreationDate": "2016-06-08T15:26:47.820", "ParentId": "37706549", "CommentCount": "7", "LastEditDate": "2016-06-08T15:30:57.653", "OwnerUserId": "1405588"}});